  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Guaran&#xED; indigenous organisations strengthening capacities in respect of access to water resources</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Integral Ecology team in the Caritas Bolivia national office will work with the local Caritas team in Camiri to provide support to Guaran&#xED; indigenous communities on issues concerning access to water and water resource management. This is a one-year project to support communities that have been affected by drought and dangerous fires in previous years. The team will provide leadership and rights training to local leaders with a particular emphasis on women and youth leaders. They will also undertake a pilot water-harvesting project to provide drinking water to one community and a pre-feasibility study of possible well locations to be used in advocacy work with local authorities.</narrative>
  </description>
